{\pard \par}{\pard{\i Note.} {\i M} and {\i SD} are used to represent mean and standard deviation, respectively. Values in square brackets indicate the 95% confidence interval for each correlation. The confidence interval is a plausible range of population correlations that could have caused the sample correlation (Cumming, 2014). * indicates {\i p} < .05. ** indicates {\i p} < .01.\par}
